“poem for Oscar losers” 
Sweet loser, I see your smile 
While the winner skips up the aisle 
He thanks his mom for no end
Waves from the stage as a friend
The flash photos are blinding 
As you clap, your teeth are grinding.
For we know that you are posin’
You’re praying he dies in an explosion.

“COOL News from Belarus” - Premiering tomorrow in Madrid. 

Inspired by a column of “weird true news items” in Minsk, Belarus. Project leader @nikitalavretski (with me + ice cream in Madrid).

My short film “I Love Me” interprets one of the tales, about a weird car theft. 

Starring CRAIG STARK * BRIAN BELL * MICHELLE STRATTON * with Ari Gold as Shlomo

 @strattosphere94 @brianbell @craigstark_ @arigold 

music by @ethangold 

Budget: pizza

Craig Stark (Hateful 8) + Brian Bell (Weezer) play drunk brothers in "I Love Me" by @arigold . Why?

Belarusian underground filmmaker @nikitalavretski asked 18 filmmakers to make cheap short films (inspired by a weekly column of weird news stories from Minsk, Belarus) for a cinema zine called "COOL (News from Belarus)", which just premiered in Madrid.

I chose a news item called “Late-night wanderer hijacks taxi,” and cast friends to interpret "Minsk in Hollywood."

Budget: pizza. 

CRAIG STARK as Tank
BRIAN BELL as Hank
MICHELLE STRATTON as Mickie
ARI GOLD as Shlomo
WALLY as Himself

Music by ETHAN GOLD @ethangold from the "Adventures of Power" soundtrack which you can hear here: https://ffm.to/adventuresofpower

“COOL (News from Belarus)” - subscribe to http://youtube.com/@coolbelarus to see the whole project. 

Inspired by ANTON SERENKEV's blurb: "A late-night wanderer hijacked a taxi with two passengers!"

Coming 2024 - "Brother Verses Brother" - an improvised movie extravaganza about music, family, the streets. With my brother @ethangold . Non-AI pro-human art. #indiefilm #independentcinema #ukulele #chinatown #brothers

as some of you know, it has been a challenging season.

a few months ago, my father and brother, for unrelated reasons, both fell seriously ill at the same time. 

I rushed to join my sisters in San Francisco in trying to save my father, and then for two weeks helping him die as beautifully as we could in his apartment.

then I rushed back to Los Angeles to help my brother, who was still in the hospital. 

I have been with him every day since then, and I am very grateful to say that @ethangold is healing - out of the hospital - beginning to plan his musical return.

in 2023, I completed a book with my father and brother, and filmed a feature film as well. “Father Verses Sons” and “Brother Verses Brother” - both of them will be coming out next year, with the help of my wonderful collaborators. (Pre-buy signed copy of the book at the link in bio if u like.)

I will be sharing some photos later because I believe that we need to look Death in the face. Perhaps instagram isn’t the place for it, but if you are reading this, then perhaps it is. 

I am deeply grateful to all of you who have held me up during these past months. 

much love going into 2024. I will be meditating with my brother this evening. Anyone in Southern California who wants to join, let me know.
